  <body>
  <h2>Use JavaScript's reduce method to get the sum of all the numbers in an array<br></h2>
    <p><i>To see the JavaScript, open dev tools (SHIFT+CTRL+I) and click on the HTML file under the "Sources" tab. Click on the "Console" tab to see the console output.  </p>
    <script>
    var numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4];

    function getSum(total, num) {
        return total + num;
    }
    
    console.log(numbers.reduce(getSum));      
    </script>
  </body>
</html
